  "text": "[27] and Wald's formula takes the explicitly gauge-invariant form Eq. (6.8). 12 Another possibility to compute the entropy would be to rewrite the HST action in a gauge-invariant manner without performing the dimensional reduction as in [CITATION_1] . We have checked that the application of this method produces the same result (6.10). As a highly non-trivial check of our computations, we have shown that the thermodynamic relation ∂S/∂M = 1/T holds at order α .",
